        <item>
            <title><![CDATA[Podlite comes to Perl: a lightweight block-based markup language for everyday use]]></title>
            <description><![CDATA[The article introduces Podlite, a new lightweight, block-based markup language that brings the readability and structure of Raku's documentation format (Pod) to the Perl ecosystem. It highlights how Podlite offers three interchangeable block styles for writing documentation within Perl code and announces its arrival via a CPAN module, positioning it as a modern tool for everyday use.]]></description>
            <pubDate>2026.01.27</pubDate>
            <guid isPermaLink="false">https://www.perl.com/article/podlite-comes-to-perl-a-lightweight-block-based-markup-language-for-everyday-use/</guid>
